        "supplementing",
        "commenting"
      ],
      "body": {
        "type": "TextualBody",
        "value": "When going to find the mirror-faced person, it is her shadow attempting to make contact that we see. This then adds a strange layer to the understanding that comes together at the end, as it is specifically the shadow-mirror-creature that the shadow of the woman attempts to make contact, as large points in the film point to the shadow being largely affected by the role of the man, and it almost brings a sense of familiarity when looking back on this scene, as the shadows would both-- if, like we saw at the beginning with the man walking into the distance, we accept that the shadow-mirror-creature is also created or affected by the man-- be the same created part of her by the man. ",
        "format": "text/plain",
        "purpose": "commenting"
      },
      "target": {
        "source": {
